WEBVTT

00:48.840 --> 00:50.341
Jin-a, are you crazy?

00:50.425 --> 00:51.968
Have you lost your mind?

00:52.343 --> 00:53.845
What about Jun-hui?

00:53.970 --> 00:55.472
Have you been toying with him?

00:56.598 --> 00:58.475
Gyeong-seon, let me explain. It's--

00:58.725 --> 01:00.018
End it with Jun-hui.

01:00.435 --> 01:01.478
Unbelievable.

01:15.950 --> 01:18.119
Gyeong-seon!

01:22.248 --> 01:23.458
Didn't you hear me?

01:23.541 --> 01:26.169
End it with Jun-hui.
That's all I have to say.

01:27.670 --> 01:30.089
Do you think I wanted to come here?

01:30.757 --> 01:32.133
You know my mom.

01:32.509 --> 01:35.428
She wouldn't back down
unless things go her way.

01:35.720 --> 01:37.847
I'm only here
so that she'll never make me--

01:37.931 --> 01:40.475
That persistent mother of yours
cannot approve of Jun-hui.

01:40.558 --> 01:42.685
You're an obedient daughter,
so just break up with him.

01:44.938 --> 01:47.148
Please don't make things worse for me.

01:48.441 --> 01:51.111
Do you seriously think
that Jun-hui and I were born for you?

01:51.694 --> 01:53.947
Why do we always have to be
understanding of you?

01:54.030 --> 01:56.241
And how much more
do we need to put up with?

01:56.574 --> 01:59.160
When it comes to Jun-hui, I don't care

02:00.036 --> 02:02.580
who I have to go against.
I don't care about anything else.

02:02.997 --> 02:05.750
You're the only reason I put up with
the way your parents treat Jun-hui.

02:05.834 --> 02:07.544
Otherwise,
I wouldn't have held myself back.

02:08.002 --> 02:10.839
But you just crossed the line.
I can't put up with this anymore.

02:11.131 --> 02:14.050
I can't put up with Jun-hui
being looked down on like this.

02:15.718 --> 02:17.720
What are you talking about?

02:18.471 --> 02:20.056
No one's looking down on him.

02:20.265 --> 02:21.349
You are.

02:22.809 --> 02:24.310
You're taking this lightly

02:24.894 --> 02:27.313
as if it's nothing more than something
to chitchat about later.

02:27.522 --> 02:30.441
Your family pities me and Jun-hui,

02:30.525 --> 02:33.486
and they aren't even ashamed to show
that they think we're not good enough.

02:33.778 --> 02:35.029
Maybe it's all in my head,

02:35.196 --> 02:37.240
but still, I'm not going to
hold myself back anymore.

02:46.166 --> 02:47.167
Ms. Yoon Jin-a?

02:49.669 --> 02:51.504
I'm your blind date.

02:57.594 --> 02:58.803
- Shall we go?
- Okay.

03:05.602 --> 03:08.521
EPISODE 12

03:14.736 --> 03:15.695
Excuse me.

03:16.654 --> 03:17.947
Let's sit here.

03:18.865 --> 03:19.908
Shall we?

03:20.450 --> 03:21.492
Take a seat.

03:22.535 --> 03:23.995
I'll sit here.

03:26.623 --> 03:27.665
Okay.

03:36.132 --> 03:37.467
Is everything all right?

03:38.134 --> 03:39.135
No.

03:39.886 --> 03:42.180
I mean, yes. I'm fine.

03:59.239 --> 04:00.615
Aren't you Jin-a?

04:05.286 --> 04:06.621
Hello.

04:06.955 --> 04:08.122
It is you, isn't it?

04:08.289 --> 04:09.123
Yes.

04:10.291 --> 04:11.876
It's been a long time, right?

04:13.795 --> 04:14.796
Yes.

04:15.296 --> 04:16.589
Gyeong-seon's over there.

04:17.173 --> 04:19.425
Yes, I know.

04:20.677 --> 04:22.011
I see.

04:23.054 --> 04:23.930
Good.

05:20.194 --> 05:22.238
Please excuse me for a second.

06:13.289 --> 06:14.373
What about Jun-hui?

06:15.374 --> 06:16.626
What about him?

06:22.715 --> 06:24.258
How long are you going to keep this up?

06:24.425 --> 06:27.386
You cannot possibly expect me
to be nice to you.

06:30.681 --> 06:32.308
Let's not waste our time like this.

06:33.101 --> 06:34.685
Let's have a constructive conversation.

06:37.605 --> 06:41.109
You sounded like you had something to say
when you called me last time.

06:42.110 --> 06:43.111
I don't.

06:44.153 --> 06:47.657
I just needed some reassurance
that Jun-hui and I weren't alone

06:47.740 --> 06:48.908
in this whole world.

06:49.408 --> 06:50.535
That was all.

06:52.537 --> 06:53.913
I'm serious.

06:54.372 --> 06:56.874
When a kid in your class
brags about his dad,

06:57.083 --> 07:00.294
you feel the urge to brag about your own.

07:00.920 --> 07:02.380
That's exactly how I felt.

07:04.048 --> 07:07.051
I thought you were old enough
not to need a parent in your life.

07:09.011 --> 07:10.596
Don't get me wrong.

07:11.180 --> 07:13.558
I know that having you in my life
would only bring me harm.

07:14.767 --> 07:15.977
But there are times

07:16.060 --> 07:17.895
that I cannot help but want your presence.

07:24.902 --> 07:26.988
It's ridiculous that people don't know

07:27.071 --> 07:29.240
how stupid those stereotypes are.

07:41.836 --> 07:42.962
I'm sorry.

07:44.255 --> 07:47.425
You do know that you're being rude, right?

07:49.469 --> 07:50.761
I'm sorry.

07:52.638 --> 07:54.265
I've been forced to go on a blind date,

07:54.348 --> 07:56.350
and I've met someone
who was forced on a blind date.

07:56.976 --> 07:58.394
But today's the worst.

08:02.148 --> 08:04.108
I don't know how to apologize to you.

08:05.943 --> 08:07.987
This means you already like someone else.

08:10.156 --> 08:13.868
If that's not the case,
it means you really don't like me.

08:14.076 --> 08:15.203
And that hurts my pride.

08:18.080 --> 08:21.000
You seem like a good guy. I mean it.

08:24.128 --> 08:26.756
Okay, let's say
you are telling me the truth.

08:28.007 --> 08:31.260
Now, what can I do
to help you feel less anxious?

08:34.138 --> 08:35.932
I don't feel anxious.

08:37.099 --> 08:39.936
That woman behind you...
Is she just your friend?

08:41.562 --> 08:45.942
Of course. She's my friend,
and she's with her dad.

08:46.526 --> 08:48.444
Then you being here
shouldn't bother her, right?

08:49.862 --> 08:52.240
Of course not. Why would you ask that?

08:53.491 --> 08:56.911
Then why does she keep glaring at us?

09:09.924 --> 09:12.134
Jin-a grew up to be a wonderful lady.

09:12.385 --> 09:14.136
She's not married yet, is she?

09:15.012 --> 09:15.972
No.

09:17.056 --> 09:18.307
Are you dating anyone?

09:21.686 --> 09:22.770
What about Jun-hui?

09:23.563 --> 09:24.897
I don't know.

09:26.440 --> 09:28.192
I'm sure he'll get married soon.

09:29.318 --> 09:31.028
Time flies so quickly.

09:32.321 --> 09:34.574
What do your children mean to you?

09:35.116 --> 09:37.493
Did you expect us to grow up on our own

09:37.577 --> 09:38.911
after we were born?

09:41.247 --> 09:43.916
You can't expect parents
to do everything for you.

09:44.458 --> 09:46.586
But you should've done
the least you could do.

09:46.877 --> 09:49.213
I had to drop out of college,
but I don't blame you for that.

09:49.297 --> 09:51.090
In the end,
I was the one who made that choice.

09:51.674 --> 09:53.384
But it's different with Jun-hui.

09:54.635 --> 09:56.637
He gave up on his dream
to become an artist

09:58.055 --> 10:00.016
and got a job at a game company
just to earn money.

10:00.266 --> 10:01.559
He didn't like me caring for him.

10:01.642 --> 10:04.061
He said he couldn't draw anything
because he felt so pressured.

10:04.729 --> 10:06.939
Do you know what the worst thing--

10:07.023 --> 10:09.025
Okay, that's enough.

10:09.108 --> 10:11.569
Don't cut me off.
I wouldn't have come here

10:11.652 --> 10:13.321
if I wasn't going to tell you all this.

10:14.113 --> 10:17.491
You probably feel sorry
for getting married multiple times,

10:17.575 --> 10:21.120
but that's not what you did wrong.
What you did wrong is

10:21.287 --> 10:23.539
that you made us grow up too fast.

10:28.210 --> 10:31.547
When we were young, I wished

10:31.631 --> 10:34.342
that Jun-hui would get himself
in some kind of trouble.

10:34.508 --> 10:37.637
I was sick and tired of him
acting all grown up.

10:38.346 --> 10:40.389
He still puts others before himself

10:40.640 --> 10:44.018
and bottles everything up inside,
and that kills me.

10:44.268 --> 10:46.520
Why did you make him become like that?
Why?

10:47.355 --> 10:48.689
Marriage?

10:49.732 --> 10:52.860
That's a luxury we can't afford
as long as you live and breathe.

10:52.943 --> 10:53.944
Do you know that?

11:31.607 --> 11:34.318
I think we should go now.

11:43.077 --> 11:44.286
How absurd.

12:15.359 --> 12:18.446
Excuse me. Let me ask you one thing.

12:19.530 --> 12:21.240
What's your relationship
with Ms. Yoon Jin-a?

12:22.408 --> 12:23.409
I'm sorry?

12:24.535 --> 12:27.371
I was her blind date today,
and I was really dumbfounded.

12:27.538 --> 12:28.831
Who exactly are you?

12:30.624 --> 12:33.461
- I'm her ex-sister-in-law.
- Pardon?

12:33.544 --> 12:35.588
Who does he think he is?

12:56.317 --> 12:57.234
3 MISSED CALLS

13:14.168 --> 13:15.753
Why don't we catch up over some tea?

13:51.580 --> 13:54.375
Do you happen to know how Jun-hui's doing?

13:56.210 --> 13:59.588
Gyeong-seon's still upset with me,
so she just left without telling me.

14:01.590 --> 14:05.094
I think he's doing well.

14:05.886 --> 14:07.263
Is he seeing anyone?

14:10.474 --> 14:12.184
Judging from what Gyeong-seon said,

14:12.268 --> 14:14.478
it feels like he's seeing someone.
Do you happen to know?

14:16.522 --> 14:17.648
I'm sorry.

14:18.816 --> 14:20.192
What's that supposed to mean?

14:23.904 --> 14:26.824
I'm sorry
that I don't know much about him.

14:30.244 --> 14:33.497
You've grown up to be way too polite.

14:36.041 --> 14:39.378
Well, I can see why since your parents
are quite old-fashioned.

14:40.629 --> 14:44.466
My parents are quite old-fashioned
and stubborn.

14:45.593 --> 14:47.428
I didn't mean it in a bad way.

14:48.470 --> 14:50.723
But it could be hard for the children
to have such parents.

14:55.644 --> 14:57.855
He seemed like your boyfriend,

14:58.355 --> 14:59.773
but I guess he wasn't--

15:00.357 --> 15:01.400
No, he's not.

15:02.484 --> 15:03.402
He's just...

15:03.986 --> 15:04.945
He was...

15:06.238 --> 15:07.615
I'm sorry.

15:08.616 --> 15:10.242
Why do you keep...

15:12.119 --> 15:15.289
I don't think you're apologizing to me
just to be polite.

15:20.002 --> 15:23.422
I don't know why,
but I just feel like apologizing to you.

15:31.722 --> 15:33.432
I need to go to the supermarket.

15:33.641 --> 15:34.683
Why?

15:35.851 --> 15:37.478
Jin-a's coming over for dinner.

15:37.978 --> 15:39.021
She's not coming.

15:40.564 --> 15:41.607
Why not?

15:41.941 --> 15:43.776
Did you talk to her? Where is she?

15:44.652 --> 15:47.613
There's no need for you to know.
She's not coming, so just come home.

15:49.281 --> 15:50.324
What's going on?

15:51.367 --> 15:53.369
Aren't you curious about
how things went with Dad?

15:53.452 --> 15:54.703
Do you only care about Jin-a?

15:56.205 --> 15:57.706
Why should I be curious?

15:58.332 --> 15:59.959
Forget it. Just come home.

16:03.587 --> 16:06.799
Where's Jin-a? I can't get a hold of her.

16:07.508 --> 16:10.803
Of course you can't.
I'll tell you later, so come home.

16:52.511 --> 16:54.596
We wouldn't see each other again,
would we?

16:55.597 --> 16:57.266
Are you not planning on coming back?

16:58.726 --> 17:00.352
Wouldn't that be better for all of us?

17:01.603 --> 17:03.731
Even though Gyeong-seon said those things,

17:04.273 --> 17:06.358
she actually misses you a lot.

17:07.359 --> 17:09.486
I'm sure Jun-hui does, too.

17:12.489 --> 17:13.657
How is Jun-hui?

17:15.034 --> 17:15.909
Sorry?

17:18.662 --> 17:21.040
I'm just wondering what kind of man
he has become.

17:25.586 --> 17:28.589
He's very warmhearted.

17:37.765 --> 17:38.974
Let our farewell be brief.

18:10.631 --> 18:11.924
Mr. Seo!

18:14.510 --> 18:15.552
Let's meet again.

18:16.136 --> 18:17.387
I insist.

18:18.764 --> 18:19.890
Meet me, at least.

18:20.974 --> 18:23.143
You have to know how Gyeong-seon
and Jun-hui are doing.

18:24.103 --> 18:25.979
They are amazing and full of life.

18:26.897 --> 18:29.608
I'll keep you updated
without telling them.

18:38.325 --> 18:39.952
You made me the offer first.

18:41.161 --> 18:44.665
I like to take the lead.

18:50.087 --> 18:51.964
- Give me a call.
- Okay.

18:54.049 --> 18:54.925
I'll get going.

18:55.384 --> 18:56.593
- Give me a call.
- I will.

19:12.025 --> 19:13.694
Oh, Jun-hui...

19:19.408 --> 19:21.910
4 MISSED CALLS

19:23.579 --> 19:24.955
Where in Bundang are you going?

19:28.625 --> 19:31.295
I'm sorry, but could you drop me off here?

19:32.880 --> 19:33.881
I'm sorry.

21:36.753 --> 21:39.089
Don't you have any pride?

21:39.631 --> 21:40.674
Stay out of this.

21:41.383 --> 21:42.801
I can't do that.

21:43.093 --> 21:44.970
What did you say? "Stay out of this"?

21:45.137 --> 21:47.055
Even if it's your life, I cannot do that.

21:47.139 --> 21:49.099
I won't tolerate it this time.

21:51.643 --> 21:52.936
Why did you have to meet him?

21:53.937 --> 21:56.398
Why did you have to go there
and find out about it?

21:57.190 --> 21:58.442
You must be out of your mind.

21:59.151 --> 22:00.902
Are you saying
she wouldn't have gotten caught

22:00.986 --> 22:02.279
had I not been there to meet Dad?

22:02.362 --> 22:04.614
You should be thankful
that I have found out about it,

22:04.698 --> 22:05.949
you stupid moron.

22:06.700 --> 22:09.745
The fact that she went on a blind date
means that they have no respect for you.

22:09.828 --> 22:11.955
They're treating you
as if you don't exist.

22:12.539 --> 22:13.749
Can't you see that?

22:13.832 --> 22:15.667
I'm about to go insane here!

22:16.543 --> 22:18.211
And do you think I'm a fool?

22:19.171 --> 22:23.008
This wouldn't have happened
out of the blue.

22:23.717 --> 22:27.054
I don't need you to tell me
to know what you had to put up with.

22:27.137 --> 22:28.305
It's obvious.

22:31.475 --> 22:32.642
What I'm saying is...

22:34.019 --> 22:35.854
whatever it was Jin-a did,

22:35.937 --> 22:38.065
it was for us to work out, not you.

22:38.774 --> 22:41.943
That's why I don't like the fact
that you found out about it.

22:43.153 --> 22:46.114
I don't like how you know everything
about me even if I don't tell you.

22:46.823 --> 22:48.867
That's driving me crazy!

22:50.869 --> 22:52.120
If you hide things from me,

22:53.413 --> 22:55.082
do you think I would be grateful for it?

22:55.874 --> 22:57.292
I will keep hiding things from you.

22:58.376 --> 22:59.753
Don't you dare!

23:04.007 --> 23:05.008
Seo Jun-hui.

23:11.223 --> 23:13.517
What else could I possibly do for you?

23:29.908 --> 23:30.951
Gosh.

23:43.839 --> 23:44.714
What did he say?

23:44.798 --> 23:46.133
What does he think of Jin-a?

23:46.383 --> 23:47.676
Is Jin-a a divorcee?

23:47.926 --> 23:51.638
What? What on earth are you talking about?

23:51.972 --> 23:53.348
You know what I'm talking about.

23:53.598 --> 23:55.767
What kind of nonsense is that?

23:56.101 --> 23:58.103
She's never even been married.
What? A divorcee?

23:58.186 --> 24:00.772
- Her ex-sister-in-law was there!
- Ex-sister-in-law?

24:01.106 --> 24:04.484
- What are you going on about?
- How could you hide such a thing from me?

24:04.609 --> 24:06.862
Hide? Hide what?

24:07.070 --> 24:09.364
Jin-a's never been married!
What are you accusing her of?

24:11.032 --> 24:13.493
Aren't you supposed to be my friend?

24:13.827 --> 24:16.955
There must have been a misunderstanding
or something.

24:17.038 --> 24:18.915
- How can you--
- I feel embarrassed

24:18.999 --> 24:20.876
- that I introduced her to him.
- What?

24:20.959 --> 24:22.335
Embarrassed to have introduced her?

24:22.544 --> 24:23.628
Embarrassed?

24:24.421 --> 24:27.507
You call my daughter a divorcee,
and you are embarrassed?

24:27.674 --> 24:29.426
My whole body is shaking with rage!

24:30.218 --> 24:31.344
What was that all about?

24:34.014 --> 24:37.017
What the hell did she say to her date?

24:37.100 --> 24:38.435
What is it?

24:39.060 --> 24:40.312
The guy she was introduced to

24:40.854 --> 24:42.397
went back to his family

24:42.814 --> 24:44.816
and said Jin-a was a divorcee.

24:44.900 --> 24:46.985
- He said he saw the sister-in-law.
- What?

24:47.194 --> 24:48.486
That little brat.

24:48.695 --> 24:51.239
This is the end for both of us.

24:51.448 --> 24:52.365
Hold on.

25:00.332 --> 25:03.752
Of course, she won't pick up.

25:04.502 --> 25:05.587
I knew it.

25:07.380 --> 25:11.218
She must be with Jun-hui right now.

25:11.468 --> 25:13.386
Gosh, that's enough.

25:13.470 --> 25:14.763
It's not enough!

25:16.473 --> 25:17.891
They wouldn't be together.

25:18.558 --> 25:21.519
Jin-a wouldn't disrespect us like that.

25:23.730 --> 25:26.608
Then what on earth happened?

25:26.691 --> 25:27.567
Just be patient.

25:27.651 --> 25:29.861
We can hear her side of the story
when she comes home.

25:59.307 --> 26:01.101
What happened today?

26:43.727 --> 26:44.978
Damn it.

29:59.672 --> 30:02.675
My gosh, it's pouring outside.
What's worse, you have a broken arm.

30:02.759 --> 30:04.010
Just stay home!

30:04.093 --> 30:05.386
I need to bring her home.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.013
Do you even know where she is?

30:07.096 --> 30:10.433
It's obvious, isn't it? She doesn't know
what kind of mistake she made

30:10.517 --> 30:13.186
because she's head over heels for Jun-hui.

30:13.269 --> 30:15.230
- I should teach her a lesson.
- My gosh.

30:15.313 --> 30:16.731
- Let go.
- That's enough!

30:20.568 --> 30:22.570
What are you going to do
if Jin-a does something bad?

30:22.654 --> 30:24.697
- She's already done enough.
- Not that.

30:25.406 --> 30:27.242
What if she ends up taking her own life?

30:27.325 --> 30:28.827
Why would you say that?

30:29.828 --> 30:30.829
Dad,

30:31.329 --> 30:33.832
do you think only certain types
of people commit suicide?

30:34.707 --> 30:36.543
Not only did I think of doing so
in high school,

30:36.751 --> 30:40.171
but I even thought about it in college
when I had a hard time adjusting.

30:41.965 --> 30:43.842
- My gosh.
- Mom, what you're doing

30:44.342 --> 30:47.262
is only going to strengthen
their relationship.

30:47.345 --> 30:50.306
What are you going to do
if they decide to run away together?

30:52.600 --> 30:53.977
You have to let go

30:54.978 --> 30:56.312
of those standards of yours.

30:56.771 --> 30:58.439
They are absurd and disappointing.

30:58.523 --> 30:59.816
Why do you say...

31:00.191 --> 31:02.485
We're not talking about
some stranger here, for God's sake!

31:02.569 --> 31:04.028
Look at your children objectively.

31:05.280 --> 31:06.614
Just like how you judge strangers.

31:07.407 --> 31:10.869
You think of strangers who don't
live up to your standards as pathetic.

31:11.578 --> 31:14.080
Well, other people certainly
think that way about me and Jin-a.

31:14.163 --> 31:16.291
That's who your children really are, Mom.

31:17.375 --> 31:19.752
And what if Jin-a ruins her life?
It's her life.

31:19.836 --> 31:21.296
Why do you keep meddling in her life?

31:21.963 --> 31:23.047
What?

31:24.132 --> 31:28.303
How could you put it that way?
I'm a parent looking out for my daughter.

31:29.888 --> 31:31.806
You're only interfering with her life.

31:32.807 --> 31:35.101
- And in a way, it's abusive.
- Seung-ho!

31:35.560 --> 31:37.312
You're making her suffer emotionally.

31:37.395 --> 31:39.188
You're tiring her out!

31:40.189 --> 31:41.441
If that's not abuse, what is?

31:44.694 --> 31:45.778
Mom.

31:46.988 --> 31:48.823
Let's not be petty.

31:49.532 --> 31:50.617
Okay?

31:51.826 --> 31:53.328
My goodness.

32:35.662 --> 32:37.538
Your mom must have been shocked.

32:42.418 --> 32:44.671
- I'm sorry that I--
- Good job.

32:46.547 --> 32:48.633
Good job for saying the right thing.

32:50.218 --> 32:51.427
But that doesn't mean

32:51.511 --> 32:54.347
you can think of your mom
as someone who's cruel to her children.

32:55.348 --> 32:57.517
Sometimes, parents can't help
but act like your mom does.

32:57.767 --> 33:00.019
No parent wants their children to suffer.

33:00.728 --> 33:02.146
I know that.

33:03.314 --> 33:05.191
But that doesn't mean

33:05.274 --> 33:07.276
parents always make the right decision.

33:07.402 --> 33:09.487
- You're right.
- So what's your point?

33:10.238 --> 33:11.656
Parents are cowards.

33:12.281 --> 33:14.993
So they all want their children
to take the safe road.

33:15.284 --> 33:17.704
They feel uneasy and anxious
when their children take risks.

33:17.829 --> 33:19.288
That's why your mom's like that.

33:19.372 --> 33:21.374
But still, she's crossing the line.

33:21.833 --> 33:23.751
And why is Jun-hui a risk?

33:25.378 --> 33:28.881
I'll try to talk things out with her.

33:32.677 --> 33:34.846
You shouldn't be so harsh on Jin-a either.

33:38.725 --> 33:40.560
Has Jun-hui contacted you?

33:42.645 --> 33:43.688
I'll try contacting him.

33:44.814 --> 33:47.608
It's just that it's pouring outside--

33:47.692 --> 33:48.860
I get it.

33:54.782 --> 33:56.826
They aren't any different.

34:19.015 --> 34:20.725
Are you with Jin-a?

34:26.481 --> 34:27.523
Where are you?

34:31.903 --> 34:32.904
Home.

35:09.440 --> 35:10.691
What are you doing here?

35:13.653 --> 35:14.695
Nothing much.

35:17.782 --> 35:20.076
You should've come inside or called...

35:25.581 --> 35:26.415
Get up.

35:28.543 --> 35:29.710
It's raining.

35:31.087 --> 35:31.921
It's the spring rain.

35:34.799 --> 35:36.050
Come on. Get up.

35:36.801 --> 35:38.511
It's pouring.

35:38.845 --> 35:40.972
I know that, so get up.

35:50.690 --> 35:51.566
What's wrong?

35:53.776 --> 35:54.944
My legs are numb.

35:59.532 --> 36:00.825
Don't try to fool me.

36:01.492 --> 36:03.578
You're only doing this
so that I won't get mad at you.

36:03.661 --> 36:05.037
No, I'm serious.

36:05.538 --> 36:06.998
My legs really feel numb.

36:12.128 --> 36:14.005
My gosh, you're driving me nuts.

36:24.473 --> 36:25.975
- It's hot.
- Okay.

36:32.481 --> 36:33.733
You're angry at me, aren't you?

36:34.859 --> 36:35.902
I was.

36:37.361 --> 36:39.155
It was clever of you to wait
until I calm down.

36:40.156 --> 36:41.866
That's not what I was doing.

36:42.867 --> 36:45.578
Then why didn't you call me?

36:48.080 --> 36:49.081
I was scared.

36:50.041 --> 36:51.083
That I might get angry?

36:53.669 --> 36:54.754
Then what?

36:56.964 --> 36:58.591
That you might ignore my call.

37:01.719 --> 37:04.597
You're being really strategic today.

37:28.120 --> 37:29.247
At times like this,

37:30.122 --> 37:32.041
it feels like you are so much younger
than me.

37:33.960 --> 37:35.127
Do I really?

37:35.211 --> 37:37.213
Look at you being cheeky.
You must feel better now.

37:47.682 --> 37:48.891
I'm sorry.

37:48.975 --> 37:50.142
You should be.

37:52.061 --> 37:54.647
- You can get angry at me.
- It's too late for that.

37:57.733 --> 37:59.568
I was going to give my mom

38:00.903 --> 38:02.863
what she wanted
for the first and last time.

38:03.447 --> 38:05.616
And I was going to use that
to stop her from forcing me

38:05.700 --> 38:07.076
to do anything in the future.

38:08.577 --> 38:09.620
But...

38:11.080 --> 38:13.040
I really should have thought it through.

38:14.083 --> 38:16.544
As soon as I saw Gyeong-seon,

38:17.128 --> 38:19.922
I realized that I had made a bad choice.

38:20.798 --> 38:22.091
Why am I so dumb?

38:22.800 --> 38:24.093
You always cause trouble.

38:25.177 --> 38:27.722
So do you hate me now?

38:27.805 --> 38:28.723
Yes,

38:29.223 --> 38:31.726
- I hate you so much that it kills me.
- What?

38:31.809 --> 38:34.061
I said you need my permission to die.

38:34.687 --> 38:35.771
I'm going to do as I please.

38:37.189 --> 38:38.107
Do what?

38:39.191 --> 38:40.943
I'm going to love you and care for you.

38:42.111 --> 38:43.446
I can't even do that?

38:45.281 --> 38:46.532
Give me two days

38:47.158 --> 38:49.952
to think about that.
I'll let you know on the day after.

38:54.498 --> 38:56.751
My gosh, you'd better stay out of trouble.

38:57.043 --> 38:59.045
I'll never cause trouble again.

39:01.380 --> 39:02.590
By the way,

39:03.966 --> 39:05.760
why did you dress up so much?

39:05.843 --> 39:07.094
You even wore earrings.

39:08.512 --> 39:09.430
Do I seem dressed up?

39:09.513 --> 39:11.390
I wear this every time
I go on a blind date.

39:11.474 --> 39:12.808
Every time you go on a blind date?

39:12.892 --> 39:14.226
You must have gone on quite a few.

39:15.227 --> 39:16.896
Think about how old I am.

39:17.104 --> 39:18.522
I've had my share of blind dates.

39:18.606 --> 39:20.274
- How many times?
- What?

39:20.358 --> 39:21.317
I can't hear you.

39:21.400 --> 39:22.735
- Answer me.
- What?

39:23.069 --> 39:24.779
Stop laughing and tell me.

39:24.904 --> 39:27.448
It's raining outside.
Let's go get ourselves in trouble.

39:27.531 --> 39:28.949
What trouble? Answer me first.

42:43.060 --> 42:44.144
I love you.

42:47.398 --> 42:49.066
Why don't you look me in the eye
and say it?

42:51.819 --> 42:54.738
Because I feel guilty
for having done some terrible things.

42:57.366 --> 43:00.619
Then you deserve to be punished.

43:00.911 --> 43:01.912
What?

45:41.113 --> 45:42.156
It's a gift.

45:47.119 --> 45:48.162
Look at you copying me.

45:48.495 --> 45:49.663
Don't you ever throw it away.

45:52.249 --> 45:53.625
You're copying me again.

45:55.085 --> 45:56.128
Shall I keep going?

45:56.503 --> 45:59.047
Gosh, I'm too head over heels for you,
Jun-hui.

46:01.800 --> 46:03.135
Go in.

46:04.052 --> 46:05.596
Yes, I should.

46:28.619 --> 46:30.245
- Bye.
- Bye. I'll get going.

46:35.626 --> 46:37.002
What's wrong with this door?

46:38.462 --> 46:39.880
- Go.
- After you get in the elevator.

46:46.553 --> 46:47.471
Bye.

46:53.310 --> 46:54.311
Bye.

47:02.402 --> 47:03.737
Go. Get going.

47:20.295 --> 47:21.338
You're late.

47:23.840 --> 47:25.592
Go in and get some rest.

48:27.487 --> 48:29.072
Did anything happen today?

48:30.282 --> 48:31.366
What do you think?

48:32.993 --> 48:34.870
But why is Mom so quiet?

48:36.246 --> 48:39.291
She either has no energy to beat you up
or thinks that it's useless.

48:41.918 --> 48:44.046
Gyeong-seon and Jun-hui found out

48:44.838 --> 48:46.798
that I went on a blind date.

48:50.552 --> 48:52.763
I ran into Gyeong-seon at the hotel.

48:55.432 --> 48:56.808
Why is it that everything you do...

48:58.477 --> 48:59.811
Are you dumb?

49:03.398 --> 49:05.942
I don't even know why I told you.

49:06.652 --> 49:07.694
About Jun-hui...

49:08.945 --> 49:10.822
You'll regret big time
if you underestimate him.

49:12.324 --> 49:13.825
Don't get on the wrong side of him.

49:14.409 --> 49:15.911
He never gives anyone a second chance.

49:16.745 --> 49:18.413
Just know who you are dealing with.

49:53.990 --> 49:54.991
Good morning.

49:55.200 --> 49:56.743
But the Mapo location is...

49:57.994 --> 50:01.832
There's nothing I can do about that.

50:02.457 --> 50:03.917
I think we should try calling him.

50:04.000 --> 50:05.335
Yes, we should.

50:05.419 --> 50:06.461
Ms. Yoon!

50:07.671 --> 50:08.755
Welcome back.

50:08.880 --> 50:10.257
I'm back in hell.

50:10.340 --> 50:12.676
It's like a battlefield
that's worse than hell.

50:12.759 --> 50:14.594
Let's fight fiercely together.

50:15.303 --> 50:17.806
But you guys only say things
that discourage me.

50:17.973 --> 50:20.642
You're back. Are you back for good?

50:21.059 --> 50:23.061
I guess you're not happy to see me.

50:23.645 --> 50:24.896
How could I be?

50:24.980 --> 50:27.357
You never help me out with anything.

50:49.087 --> 50:50.672
Would you like a cup of coffee?

50:51.006 --> 50:53.425
Coffee sounds good.
I'd like an Americano, please.

50:53.717 --> 50:54.676
Okay.

51:06.563 --> 51:10.525
I submitted my statement
with assailants' names

51:10.609 --> 51:11.818
to Ms. Jeong via email.

51:13.528 --> 51:14.529
I see.

51:15.405 --> 51:16.782
What's up with that reaction?

51:18.366 --> 51:19.493
I feel bad.

51:20.243 --> 51:23.246
I took part in making you step up
and make a statement.

51:26.625 --> 51:28.710
You always think
that I'm the easy target, don't you?

51:28.794 --> 51:29.878
No, that's not true.

51:30.796 --> 51:33.006
I couldn't force others
because they're so scared.

51:33.590 --> 51:36.676
I tried to intimidate them,
but they didn't even budge.

51:36.760 --> 51:39.596
Right, and you thought
it'd be easy to persuade me.

51:40.180 --> 51:42.808
Frankly, I used to think like that,
but not anymore.

51:43.266 --> 51:45.393
You know that you have
invincible power now.

51:45.811 --> 51:47.729
Everyone is just saying that,
but it's not true.

51:47.813 --> 51:48.980
Invincible, my foot.

51:52.317 --> 51:54.611
Anyway, it must've taken you
a lot of courage to do that.

51:55.320 --> 51:56.321
I'm impressed.

51:56.404 --> 51:58.615
It's too early to compliment me like that.

51:59.991 --> 52:03.245
Why do you say that?
Do you think it'll affect many people?

52:05.121 --> 52:08.124
I'm sure it would.
I mean, it's not a small issue.

52:12.128 --> 52:15.382
- Jin-a, if...
- Gosh, let's not think about anything.

52:15.465 --> 52:16.591
I don't want to feel anxious.

52:17.008 --> 52:18.593
I'll deal with it as it comes.

52:19.094 --> 52:21.221
- That's fine, but--
- No, don't.

52:22.097 --> 52:25.100
We'll do a good job so that nothing bad
will happen. We can sort it all out.

52:25.350 --> 52:27.936
They say positive thinking
yields positive outcomes. It'll be fine.

52:29.855 --> 52:32.566
You're worried about something else,
aren't you?

52:35.151 --> 52:36.778
Everyone has worries.

52:36.862 --> 52:39.865
Let's only think about work
when we're here. We should get back.

52:44.953 --> 52:46.162
I guess...

52:47.539 --> 52:49.124
I underestimated Yoon Jin-a.

52:50.959 --> 52:53.420
I'm sure it took her
quite a lot of courage to do this.

52:53.753 --> 52:54.838
That's not what I meant.

52:55.505 --> 52:57.215
She's quite tenacious.

52:58.341 --> 53:00.886
Who would put up with that for ten years?

53:01.136 --> 53:02.470
Most people would've gone bonkers.

53:04.431 --> 53:06.057
You trained her well.

53:08.059 --> 53:09.895
It doesn't sound like a compliment.

53:09.978 --> 53:12.939
Of course it's not.
Dealing with you is hard enough,

53:13.398 --> 53:15.525
but you've groomed her
into your successor.

53:19.988 --> 53:21.072
But you see,

53:21.865 --> 53:25.785
I'm not sure if Yoon Jin-a
would be okay if this gets out.

53:27.078 --> 53:30.081
I'm not quite sure
what you're trying to say, sir.

53:30.790 --> 53:32.500
I don't have any hidden intentions.

53:32.584 --> 53:34.252
I'm really worried about her, that's all.

53:35.045 --> 53:35.962
Think about it.

53:36.129 --> 53:38.882
No one would just sit back and watch
when their job is at risk.

53:39.966 --> 53:43.053
Sometimes, the assailant
can become a victim along the way.

53:43.136 --> 53:46.014
In a crisis, people can do
whatever it takes to survive.

53:47.390 --> 53:48.391
Aren't I right?

53:50.810 --> 53:54.481
We should make sure it doesn't
turn into a situation like that.

53:55.899 --> 53:57.651
Aren't we on the same page, sir?

53:57.901 --> 53:58.860
Yes, of course.

53:59.736 --> 54:01.071
We'll make sure it doesn't happen.

54:12.707 --> 54:15.585
Mr. Kong? Kong Cheol-gu is...

54:16.002 --> 54:18.463
Is he instigating you guys to say...
Is that what he's doing?

54:19.172 --> 54:21.591
I'm not sure if "instigating"
is the right word,

54:22.133 --> 54:25.011
but he said that he only did
what he did to the female employees

54:26.930 --> 54:28.682
because of...

54:29.849 --> 54:30.850
Because of what?

54:31.434 --> 54:35.271
He said he had no choice but to do it
because of your request.

54:36.231 --> 54:38.233
That son of a...

54:45.240 --> 54:46.324
What else did he say?

54:46.908 --> 54:50.078
He's been contacting the female employees
who left the company as well--

54:50.161 --> 54:51.579
- Hey!
- Yes?

54:53.248 --> 54:55.667
Sorry, I'm not mad at you.

54:56.751 --> 54:57.836
That son of a bitch.

54:58.253 --> 55:00.171
I mean, Kong...

55:01.965 --> 55:03.800
- Gosh.
- Are you okay, Mr. Nam?

55:11.641 --> 55:12.726
I have to be okay.

55:14.227 --> 55:15.353
Only then, I'll be able to...

55:17.105 --> 55:18.148
How should I put it?

55:19.024 --> 55:20.025
Right, support you.

55:22.610 --> 55:23.611
And Kong Cheol-gu...

55:24.696 --> 55:25.780
I must...

55:27.323 --> 55:29.159
teach him a serious lesson.

55:35.457 --> 55:36.708
Soon,

55:38.168 --> 55:40.128
you and I will become rivals.

55:41.713 --> 55:42.630
Rivals?

55:44.299 --> 55:47.469
Mr. Nam will get fired soon. That means
someone will get promoted to his position.

55:47.677 --> 55:50.138
I think it will be either you or me.

55:53.016 --> 55:55.101
- Are you already excited about it?
- Well...

55:56.269 --> 55:58.897
Don't you think you should
worry about yourself a little?

55:59.272 --> 56:00.648
Hey, don't you know me?

56:01.608 --> 56:04.069
I already won all the female employees
over to my side,

56:04.152 --> 56:05.904
including those
who already left the company.

56:06.905 --> 56:08.198
Oh, boy.

56:09.240 --> 56:11.910
Soon, we won't be able to see Mr. Nam
in this building.

56:17.540 --> 56:18.958
Why are you staring at me like that?

56:19.334 --> 56:20.835
I just want to get a good look at you.

56:21.961 --> 56:23.046
What does that mean?

56:23.797 --> 56:25.673
I just wanted
to get a good look at you now

56:26.174 --> 56:29.094
in case you end up
moving high up in the ladder soon.

56:30.720 --> 56:32.889
If that happens,
you are the first one I'll help out.

56:32.972 --> 56:34.974
Gosh, don't worry about me.

56:35.391 --> 56:38.228
Just hearing that is enough.

56:48.029 --> 56:50.949
Gyeong-seon is ignoring all of my calls

56:51.032 --> 56:52.242
and messages.

56:53.284 --> 56:54.619
Leave her alone for a while.

56:54.869 --> 56:56.204
She'll be fine in a bit.

56:57.122 --> 56:58.289
Should I not go see her?

56:58.373 --> 57:00.041
Well, you can if you want.

57:01.084 --> 57:02.168
You don't think I should.

57:03.503 --> 57:04.921
Shall I take you to her place?

57:06.840 --> 57:09.926
Gosh,
you always put me on the spot like this.

57:11.636 --> 57:13.304
It's because I lack in many ways.

57:15.974 --> 57:18.017
Why are you saying that out of the blue?

57:18.685 --> 57:20.228
I was just joking.

57:20.311 --> 57:21.855
It's not funny at all.

57:22.856 --> 57:24.858
You told me not to be insecure.

57:24.941 --> 57:26.151
Why are you all insecure?

57:26.860 --> 57:28.611
Sorry, I won't be like that again.

57:34.367 --> 57:36.995
Don't be mad. You're making me
feel like I'm a total loser.

57:37.078 --> 57:38.288
Who said you're a loser?

57:39.831 --> 57:42.750
The guy I like isn't a loser.

57:42.834 --> 57:44.502
Don't talk about my boyfriend like that

57:44.586 --> 57:46.796
when you don't even know him that well.

57:49.924 --> 57:51.843
Did you just laugh? How dare you!

57:53.720 --> 57:55.847
My gosh, what should I do about you?

57:56.181 --> 57:57.223
What?

57:58.141 --> 58:00.268
Just adore me

58:04.022 --> 58:05.023
Gosh.

58:09.944 --> 58:10.987
What are you looking for?

58:11.154 --> 58:13.198
Your mom asked me to take out the meat

58:13.281 --> 58:15.575
for the soup she'll make
tomorrow morning, but I can't...

58:18.036 --> 58:19.454
Mom, your cast is removed.

58:34.928 --> 58:36.429
When did she get her cast removed?

59:37.282 --> 59:39.325
Can I meet Jun-hui?

59:55.925 --> 59:59.178
Do you want to meet Dad?

01:00:30.501 --> 01:00:31.628
Don't worry about us.

01:00:32.128 --> 01:00:33.588
Jun-hui and I will be fine

01:00:33.796 --> 01:00:36.174
just like how we've been all these years.

01:00:36.507 --> 01:00:38.134
They are such brats.

01:00:55.443 --> 01:00:56.444
I wondered why you said

01:00:56.527 --> 01:00:58.988
we should go for a walk after lunch.

01:00:59.405 --> 01:01:00.782
How did you hear about this place?

01:01:00.865 --> 01:01:03.409
Ms. Kang told me about it.
We wanted to check it out together,

01:01:03.493 --> 01:01:05.495
but she's had plans
for lunch and dinner all week.

01:01:07.330 --> 01:01:09.165
Something must be up with Se-yeong.

01:01:09.666 --> 01:01:10.667
Why?

01:01:11.584 --> 01:01:13.127
She's not acting weird or anything,

01:01:13.878 --> 01:01:15.588
but I sense that something's off
about her.

01:01:16.172 --> 01:01:17.256
Anyway, that's how I feel.

01:01:19.175 --> 01:01:20.259
She's like a swan.

01:01:20.927 --> 01:01:22.053
- A swan?
- A swan?

01:01:22.136 --> 01:01:23.221
What's that?

01:01:23.554 --> 01:01:25.348
She always seems calm and composed,

01:01:25.431 --> 01:01:28.393
but she's busy paddling away underwater.

01:01:29.143 --> 01:01:30.603
That's what guys do though.

01:01:31.187 --> 01:01:32.313
Not girls?

01:01:34.482 --> 01:01:36.818
Let's say a guy went clubbing
without telling his girlfriend.

01:01:37.151 --> 01:01:38.277
How did he do it?

01:01:38.361 --> 01:01:40.113
He'd sit in his car

01:01:40.363 --> 01:01:43.074
and close all the windows.
Then he'd cover his phone with his clothes

01:01:43.157 --> 01:01:44.992
to shut out all the noise.

01:01:45.076 --> 01:01:46.536
"Yes, I'm going to bed now.

01:01:46.619 --> 01:01:47.995
Sweet dreams, darling."

01:01:48.079 --> 01:01:49.497
He'd even recline in his car seat

01:01:49.580 --> 01:01:51.040
to make her believe it.

01:01:51.249 --> 01:01:52.834
Let's say the girlfriend keeps talking.

01:01:53.418 --> 01:01:55.586
Then he'd be like,
"Get some sleep for tomorrow

01:01:55.712 --> 01:01:57.088
so that your skin can glow."

01:01:57.422 --> 01:01:59.799
He'd make it sound like
he's doing it for her.

01:02:00.299 --> 01:02:01.467
Then mission accomplished.

01:02:01.551 --> 01:02:04.011
- I'd just give up on going clubbing.
- Me too.

01:02:04.345 --> 01:02:05.638
Men lie all the time

01:02:05.722 --> 01:02:07.557
to accomplish their goals.

01:02:09.142 --> 01:02:11.185
Who wrote the book you're reading?

01:02:11.269 --> 01:02:12.437
You should be careful too.

01:02:12.729 --> 01:02:14.063
Mr. Seo...

01:02:15.440 --> 01:02:18.109
- Should I call him your future husband?
- Cut it out.

01:02:19.610 --> 01:02:22.196
Anyway, all men have secrets.

01:02:22.280 --> 01:02:23.614
Dozens of secrets, actually.

01:02:26.284 --> 01:02:29.162
Is there a way
to find out about their secrets?

01:02:29.328 --> 01:02:30.663
That will only cause trouble.

01:02:30.747 --> 01:02:31.664
Why?

01:02:31.831 --> 01:02:33.541
It's no longer a secret once it's out.

01:02:34.041 --> 01:02:35.960
Their pride is built around that.

01:02:36.544 --> 01:02:38.212
Apparently, you should act like

01:02:38.296 --> 01:02:39.797
you know nothing even if you find out.

01:02:41.424 --> 01:02:43.551
Are men really such complicated creatures?

01:02:44.510 --> 01:02:45.636
I have no idea.

01:02:46.262 --> 01:02:47.597
I can't trust what she's saying.

01:02:48.264 --> 01:02:49.557
I read about it in a book.

01:02:50.141 --> 01:02:51.684
The one you tried on looked good on you.

01:02:52.185 --> 01:02:53.436
- You should buy it.
- You buy me.

01:02:54.145 --> 01:02:56.022
Me? I'm sure I make a lot less than you.

01:02:56.814 --> 01:02:58.316
- Not really.
- Hello.

01:02:58.900 --> 01:03:00.067
- Hello.
- Hello.

01:03:00.151 --> 01:03:01.736
It's so nice to see you, Ms. Yoon.

01:03:03.112 --> 01:03:04.155
He's obnoxious.

01:03:06.073 --> 01:03:07.450
Have you watched this movie?

01:03:08.242 --> 01:03:09.243
No, I haven't.

01:03:09.368 --> 01:03:11.245
- Let's watch it together.
- I don't want to.

01:03:11.996 --> 01:03:13.122
Okay.

01:03:13.247 --> 01:03:14.665
- Sorry.
- Right, you have a boyfriend.

01:03:15.208 --> 01:03:16.709
- I'll watch it alone.
- You can join us.

01:03:16.959 --> 01:03:18.252
Let's go watch it, Ms. Geum.

01:03:19.754 --> 01:03:20.630
Let's get on.

01:03:21.172 --> 01:03:22.423
What? Is something wrong?

01:03:23.007 --> 01:03:24.634
Is Jun-hui going abroad again?

01:03:25.635 --> 01:03:26.636
Who said that?

01:03:26.803 --> 01:03:28.513
The Chinese people said that just now.

01:03:29.847 --> 01:03:30.848
What exactly did they say?

01:03:31.140 --> 01:03:32.517
One of them asked if the guy

01:03:32.600 --> 01:03:35.102
who was in the States
will participate in the project,

01:03:35.269 --> 01:03:36.354
and they said, "Probably."

01:03:36.479 --> 01:03:37.855
He didn't think the guy was coming,

01:03:38.105 --> 01:03:39.232
but they said he'd be there

01:03:39.315 --> 01:03:41.275
and that he can stay
for however long it takes.

01:03:44.278 --> 01:03:45.780
I guess Ms. Yoon didn't know about it.

01:03:59.544 --> 01:04:00.670
Have you eaten yet?

01:04:02.505 --> 01:04:04.257
Shall we meet on the rooftop
for some coffee?

01:04:09.345 --> 01:04:10.555
Are you busy?

01:05:07.111 --> 01:05:10.156
Oh, no. You must be upset
that I didn't read your texts.

01:05:10.323 --> 01:05:11.490
How should I make up for it?

01:05:12.825 --> 01:05:13.826
Are you crazy?

01:05:14.493 --> 01:05:16.871
I'm going to do it one day.

01:05:17.121 --> 01:05:18.331
Have you been busy?

01:05:19.206 --> 01:05:20.207
No.

01:05:20.750 --> 01:05:22.668
A meeting got scheduled,
so I couldn't pick up.

01:05:22.752 --> 01:05:24.128
About the project in China?

01:05:24.712 --> 01:05:25.838
How did you know?

01:05:26.088 --> 01:05:27.506
Are you going on a business trip?

01:05:28.299 --> 01:05:29.550
Do you have a spy at our office?

01:05:29.634 --> 01:05:30.718
When are you leaving?

01:05:31.302 --> 01:05:32.428
I'm not going.

01:05:32.511 --> 01:05:34.931
It'll be at least for three months.
I can't live without you.

01:05:35.222 --> 01:05:36.641
I said I'd never go.

01:05:37.058 --> 01:05:38.726
Why did you say that?

01:05:39.435 --> 01:05:42.813
I can take a leave and go with you.

01:05:42.897 --> 01:05:45.066
Think about it.
I wouldn't have to care about anything.

01:05:45.149 --> 01:05:47.151
I would be free from everything.

01:05:49.820 --> 01:05:50.905
Freedom.

01:05:51.155 --> 01:05:52.698
You must be under a lot of stress.

01:05:56.494 --> 01:05:58.746
I was just saying.

01:05:59.789 --> 01:06:01.958
Let's have fun today.
Do you have anything in mind?

01:06:02.458 --> 01:06:03.793
Should we watch a movie?

01:06:03.876 --> 01:06:06.337
Sounds good.
Pick a movie you want to watch.

01:06:07.630 --> 01:06:10.424
What should we watch?
I wonder what's in theaters these days.

01:06:17.556 --> 01:06:18.641
Hello?

01:06:23.562 --> 01:06:25.898
One second. I'll be right back.

01:06:50.840 --> 01:06:53.551
I don't think we can
watch a movie tonight.

01:06:54.427 --> 01:06:56.679
- Who was that?
- It was Dad.

01:06:56.929 --> 01:07:00.808
My mom caught a cold,
so he wants me to come home early.

01:07:02.476 --> 01:07:04.478
Then you should go home. Let's get going.

01:07:08.649 --> 01:07:09.859
What time do you get off work?

01:07:11.861 --> 01:07:13.404
I'm not sure. Soon?

01:07:14.989 --> 01:07:16.490
Call me. I'll give you a ride.

01:07:16.657 --> 01:07:17.742
No, it's okay.

01:07:19.744 --> 01:07:20.995
You are not going home, are you?

01:07:22.621 --> 01:07:23.831
Are you doubting me?

01:07:25.750 --> 01:07:26.917
Just go, wherever it is.

01:07:45.186 --> 01:07:46.228
How's this?

01:07:46.896 --> 01:07:48.564
- Doesn't this one look too strong?
- It does.

01:07:48.731 --> 01:07:50.816
Take a look at this. How's this?

01:07:51.025 --> 01:07:53.694
- This is too plain.
- It looks like we copied something.

01:07:53.778 --> 01:07:54.987
It's too boring.

01:07:55.738 --> 01:07:57.323
Don't you think this one looks better?

01:07:57.490 --> 01:08:00.284
It's not even the main character,
but it leaves a big impression.

01:08:02.036 --> 01:08:03.370
That's not bad either.

01:08:20.596 --> 01:08:21.764
Here, take a look.

01:08:25.101 --> 01:08:26.769
- I'm getting off work. Hang in there.
- Here.

01:08:26.852 --> 01:08:29.063
Enjoy your dinner. Kisses.

01:08:31.398 --> 01:08:33.776
And this one too.

01:08:36.987 --> 01:08:37.988
What?

01:08:48.624 --> 01:08:50.751
I could've come to you.

01:08:50.835 --> 01:08:53.587
I'm the one taking away your time.
This is the least I can do.

01:08:53.671 --> 01:08:54.964
I have a lot of time to spare.

01:08:55.422 --> 01:08:58.467
You shouldn't waste
such precious time of your life.

01:08:59.009 --> 01:09:00.302
You should go on dates.

01:09:00.845 --> 01:09:02.012
My boyfriend...

01:09:03.931 --> 01:09:06.016
Did he give you permission to see me?

01:09:08.519 --> 01:09:10.020
Don't make me look like the bad guy.

01:09:10.396 --> 01:09:12.690
- I won't. You haven't eaten, right?
- Right.

01:09:12.773 --> 01:09:15.025
I know a quiet place nearby.
What do you say?

01:09:15.317 --> 01:09:17.903
I have no idea
where anything is around here.

01:09:17.987 --> 01:09:19.572
I will guide you.

01:09:21.073 --> 01:09:22.241
Come on.

01:09:23.159 --> 01:09:24.660
It's this way.

01:09:35.045 --> 01:09:36.088
Hey.

01:09:37.214 --> 01:09:38.382
Where are you going?

01:09:39.341 --> 01:09:40.676
I'm going home.

01:09:47.099 --> 01:09:48.642
Can you see me?

01:09:55.107 --> 01:09:56.734
The thing is...

01:09:57.318 --> 01:09:58.277
Just come here.

01:10:00.196 --> 01:10:01.405
Jun-hui.

01:10:02.907 --> 01:10:04.074
Just come here.

01:10:04.658 --> 01:10:05.826
Don't be like that.

01:10:06.994 --> 01:10:08.662
Didn't you hear me?

01:10:36.857 --> 01:10:39.526
I can't reach him.
He didn't even go to work.

01:10:39.777 --> 01:10:41.278
- Gosh.
- I thought you two broke up.

01:10:41.362 --> 01:10:43.656
- He's hurt?
- What do you not like about Jun-hui?

01:10:44.698 --> 01:10:46.617
- I think it's wonderful
- My goodness.

01:10:46.700 --> 01:10:48.786
that you are going out with Jun-hui.

01:10:48.869 --> 01:10:51.747
Don't you know what your father is like?
You two won't be any different.

01:10:51.914 --> 01:10:53.874
Someone who I never want to see again
shows up

01:10:53.958 --> 01:10:54.959
and acts like a parent.

01:10:55.042 --> 01:10:56.585
Even worse, in front of a woman I love.

01:10:56.669 --> 01:10:59.129
- He's still your father.
- What do you mean they were persuaded?

01:10:59.213 --> 01:11:01.298
Jin-a was way too much of a pushover.

01:11:01.382 --> 01:11:03.676
I can make you pay
for something you didn't even do.

01:11:03.759 --> 01:11:06.262
- Would you like that?
- How could you hurt him like this?

01:11:06.345 --> 01:11:08.973
I will break up with him. I will.

01:11:09.765 --> 01:11:10.808
Jun-hui.

01:11:11.976 --> 01:11:13.727
Let's end it here.

01:11:17.398 --> 01:11:19.400
Subtitle translation by Kim Su-hyeon
